            {"question": "What is 'informational interviewing'?", "options": ["A formal job interview", "A conversation with a professional to learn about their role/industry (not to ask for a job)", "An interview conducted via email", "A group discussion"], "correct_index": 1, "explanation": "Informational interviews are exploratory conversations to learn about industries, roles, and career paths — not to ask for jobs directly."},
            {"question": "How should you dress for a formal interview in India?", "options": ["Casual jeans and t-shirt", "Clean formals — pressed shirt/blouse, trousers/skirt, polished shoes", "Ethnic festive wear", "Athleisure"], "correct_index": 1, "explanation": "For formal interviews in India, crisp formals convey professionalism and respect for the opportunity."},
            {"question": "What is the ideal font and size for a resume?", "options": ["Comic Sans, 16pt", "Professional fonts like Calibri/Arial, 10-12pt", "Times New Roman, 8pt", "Any decorative font, any size"], "correct_index": 1, "explanation": "Professional, readable fonts (Calibri, Arial, Garamond) in 10-12pt ensure ATS compatibility and readability."},
            {"question": "What question should you always ask at the end of an interview?", "options": ["'How much vacation do I get?'", "'What does success look like in this role in the first 90 days?'", "'Can I leave early on Fridays?'", "'Do you have free food?'"], "correct_index": 1, "explanation": "Asking about expectations and success metrics shows genuine interest in contributing and excelling in the role."},
            {"question": "What is a 'portfolio' in the context of job applications?", "options": ["A financial investment document", "A curated collection of your work samples demonstrating skills and achievements", "A bag for carrying resumes", "Your social media profile"], "correct_index": 1, "explanation": "A portfolio showcases tangible work samples, projects, and achievements that demonstrate your capabilities."},
            {"question": "How do you handle an unexpected or difficult interview question?", "options": ["Panic and stay silent", "Take a moment to think, ask for clarification if needed, then answer thoughtfully", "Make up an answer immediately", "Walk out of the interview"], "correct_index": 1, "explanation": "It's professional to take a moment to think — interviewers appreciate thoughtful responses over rushed ones."},
            {"question": "What is 'applicant ghosting'?", "options": ["A ghost applying for jobs", "When a candidate stops responding to an employer without explanation", "When a company doesn't respond after an interview", "A Halloween hiring event"], "correct_index": 1, "explanation": "Ghosting — disappearing without communication — is unprofessional and damages your reputation in the industry."},
